hey are being brought to market. The DSM adapts quickly to continuous changes in a digital organization that evolves quickly over time. Creates a culture of one team mentality and strong communication on successes and opportunities.This field-based position requires &gt;60% travel, working closely with regional Commercial Managers, Directors and Global Distribution and customers across the assigned region.Manage/support regional digital sales team by being involved in the hiring, training, developing, and retaining top talent to drive the digital sales activities across the Worldwide Indirect markets globally.Manage/support all commercial activities, from lead generation to closing the deal and post sales account management for Digital expansions and dV5 Digital implementations.Provide technical, functional and product expertise to team members.Execute the digital sales strategy in the assigned region, by developing and implementing sales activities to achieve and exceed goals set by senior management.Expand usage of digital in top digital customer targets in close alignment with the capital and clinical sales teams across the Distribution markets.Manage and increase the day-to-day customer and account relations.Build and maintain excellent relationship and collaborate closely with da Vinci commercial sales teams in Distribution markets, corporate marketing, regional marketing, field service, and enabling functions (contracting, data privacy, tendering, marketing, customer service, customer success, etc.) to implement new strategies and programs as directed by senior management.Diagnose knowledge gaps within the team and implement training plans accordingly.Develop annual goals and forecasting and provide regular reporting to the upper management.Review results quarterly with senior leadership to allow for agility in this rapidly growing business segment.Create a culture of solutions and support to help expand the Digital footprint to all Intuitive markets and customers.Support and lead Worldwide Indirect digital projects.Collaborate with Global Digital team members in EU, US, APAC and LATAM regularly.QualificationsRoles and Responsibilities:Required Knowledge, Skills, And ExperienceAdvanced degree (M.Sc., PhD and/or MD) or equivalent experience required. Engineering, life science or medical background preferred.Minimum of 8 years sales experience including 5+ years in medical device sales.Minimum 2 years of experience in selling and implementing digital solutions to hospitals.Experience in developing, coaching, and training sales or clinical support roles in the medical device industry is an advantage.Deep understanding of clinical workflows in the OR (Surgery, Endoscopy), IT infrastructure and EMR / PACS solutions.Result-driven with a strong sense of accountability, agility and collaboration.Experienced in working with Clinical KOLs in Robotic Surgery, surgery, endoscopy and digital solutions.Demonstrated ability to influence, build and lead a team is preferred.Excellent verbal and written communication in English required. Other language skills a plus.&gt;60% travel expected.Additional InformationIntuitive is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. We provide equal employment opportunities to all qualified applicants and employees, and prohibit discrimination and harassment of any type, without regard to race, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, color, age, religion, protected veteran or disability status, genetic information or any other status protected under federal, state, or local applicable laws.We will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in accordance with fair chance laws."}
