resentation skills with the ability to explain complex concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.  Strong written communication skills, including email correspondence, technical documentation, and RFP responses. Problem-Solving And Collaboration Proven ability to analyze customer challenges and creatively design tailored solutions.  Collaborative mindset, working effectively across sales, product, and engineering teams. Nice-to-Have Qualifications Experience in vulnerability management, penetration testing, or incident response.  Knowledge of regulatory requirements such as PCI DSS, GDPR, APPI and SOC-2.  Certifications in relevant technologies or familiarity with OWASP API Top 10.  Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools (e.g., CI/CD pipelines, Helm, Terraform).  Why Join Akamai? At Akamai, you’ll join a collaborative and innovative team dedicated to solving some of the most pressing cybersecurity challenges facing enterprises today. You’ll have the opportunity to work with industry-leading solutions, engage with high-profile customers, and grow as a thought leader in API security.You’ll also play a key role in empowering your colleagues, acting as a subject matter expert on API security to ensure that the entire team stays ahead of evolving threats and technologies."}
